WEBVTT

00:04.520 --> 00:07.120
Please be aware, Mr Shelby,
that the deaths of your people

00:07.120 --> 00:09.160
are your own responsibility.

00:09.160 --> 00:11.120
Since my mother
passed away four years ago,

00:11.120 --> 00:12.520
Tommy and I haven't even spoken.

00:12.520 --> 00:15.200
I'm very much looking forward to
working with you again, Michael.

00:15.200 --> 00:18.200
That, my friend, is the finest opium
in the world.

00:18.200 --> 00:20.840
Why would you sell? The Irish
are being difficult.

00:20.840 --> 00:22.200
The Italians are not an option.

00:22.200 --> 00:25.360
You're going to America? To Canada,
to collect payment for the shipment.

00:25.360 --> 00:27.760
Elizabeth,
you are a very lucky woman,

00:27.760 --> 00:29.920
to have each day what
I have only sampled once.

00:29.920 --> 00:32.440
Mr Shelby,
your daughter has consumption.

00:32.440 --> 00:34.600
She's gone, Tommy. She's gone.

00:34.600 --> 00:36.840
A daughter lost. A son found.

00:36.840 --> 00:38.880
This is my son.
They call him Duke.

00:38.880 --> 00:42.640
It is tuberculoma.
I am afraid it is inoperable.

00:42.640 --> 00:44.560
How long? Perhaps 18 months.

00:44.560 --> 00:47.160
My associates are going
to take care of Thomas Shelby,

00:47.160 --> 00:49.080
and you are going
to give us his brother.

00:49.080 --> 00:51.680
What are Michael's real intentions
towards me, Gina?

00:51.680 --> 00:53.560
And if you lie, I will know.

00:53.560 --> 00:56.000
It is my intention
to kill Tommy Shelby.

00:57.160 --> 01:02.200
This programme contains
scenes of Repetitive Flashing Images

01:02.200 --> 01:07.400
and some scenes which some viewers
may find upsetting,

01:07.400 --> 01:13.040
and very strong language and some
violent scenes from the start.

01:22.120 --> 01:26.800
It was the ambitions and strategies
of one man that caused this.

01:26.800 --> 01:29.560
I will take revenge
on Tommy Shelby.

01:58.840 --> 02:02.640
Do you want a drink first
or a whore first?

02:04.080 --> 02:06.880
I want to see my wife first.

02:06.880 --> 02:08.560
After you've fucked your wife,

02:08.560 --> 02:11.080
you're going to kill a man,
right?

02:40.280 --> 02:41.760
DOOR OPENS

02:41.760 --> 02:43.320
SNIFFLING

02:56.560 --> 02:59.040
The smoke
from your daughter's funeral

02:59.040 --> 03:01.000
is still in your clothes...

03:02.360 --> 03:04.480
...and you slept with someone.

03:06.960 --> 03:09.920
Not just someone.

03:09.920 --> 03:11.400
The enemy.

03:12.800 --> 03:15.920
Every enemy we ever had
in one woman.

03:17.920 --> 03:21.320
There are some things
that I do, Lizzie, that I...

03:21.320 --> 03:24.160
You're not so good
at lying any more, Tommy.

03:24.160 --> 03:27.240
These days,
the truth gets in your eyes.

03:30.160 --> 03:32.360
I have to go to Canada, Lizzie.

03:33.720 --> 03:37.440
I need to know where you will go.
See? You just accept it.

03:38.680 --> 03:40.560
You don't fight it.

03:42.880 --> 03:44.560
You ARE cursed, Tommy.

03:46.920 --> 03:51.200
Never to understand the limits
that other people will accept.

03:53.760 --> 03:57.280
Never to be allowed in
where everybody else is.

04:00.760 --> 04:03.200
A curse never to be lifted.

04:04.520 --> 04:06.680
I will be away, Lizzie.

04:08.320 --> 04:10.720
And while I'm gone,
I know a place where...

04:10.720 --> 04:13.360
Always gone, always away.

04:15.240 --> 04:17.560
Well, now your rings are gone,

04:17.560 --> 04:19.840
your rings are away.

04:19.840 --> 04:21.800
I'm already packed.

04:25.720 --> 04:28.560
Now leave me to say goodbye
to Ruby.

04:41.960 --> 04:44.720
I have to go away for a bit,
Charlie.

04:51.520 --> 04:53.680
Look at me.

04:53.680 --> 04:55.600
Hey. Look at me.

05:00.240 --> 05:03.720
Mum already told me
she's leaving...

05:03.720 --> 05:06.000
..and she told me why.

05:15.800 --> 05:18.480
Mum, where are you going?

05:22.000 --> 05:23.680
A hotel.

05:23.680 --> 05:26.560
And then your father
will get me a house.

05:31.400 --> 05:34.880
Mum, I'll come with you.

05:36.240 --> 05:38.520
I'd rather be with you.

05:38.520 --> 05:39.760
Wherever it is.

05:41.280 --> 05:42.560
You're not my mum...

05:44.120 --> 05:46.680
..but you're more my mum
than he's my dad.

05:48.480 --> 05:50.200
He's never here.

05:52.120 --> 05:54.720
I'd be on my own here.

05:54.720 --> 05:56.440
Oh, Charles, love...

05:58.480 --> 06:01.360
..I don't think your father
would allow that.

06:04.280 --> 06:06.680
You can go.

06:06.680 --> 06:08.400
You can go, son.

06:09.880 --> 06:11.640
I know a good place.

06:11.640 --> 06:14.000
Lizzie,
I'll arrange that place.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.920
And, Charlie,
you can take him, eh?

06:18.320 --> 06:20.800
They have stables
at this new place.

06:20.800 --> 06:24.080
After a while, he'll...
He'll listen to you.

06:24.080 --> 06:26.520
He'll forget about Ruby.

06:26.520 --> 06:28.400
That's how horses are.

06:29.760 --> 06:32.600
And you'll be here all alone.

06:32.600 --> 06:36.120
I'm buying land, Lizzie.
I'm buying up land.

06:36.120 --> 06:37.960
This place I've bought

06:37.960 --> 06:41.680
I was going to knock down,
but you can go there. Dad...

06:44.600 --> 06:46.760
Where will you go?

06:52.520 --> 06:54.200
KEYS CLANK

06:54.200 --> 06:56.800
This is
the Peaky Blinders' armoury.

06:56.800 --> 06:59.400
We have
a very good relationship

06:59.400 --> 07:01.760
with the BSA factory
in Armoury Road.

07:03.720 --> 07:08.280
Two dozen machine guns,
half a dozen sub-machine guns,

07:08.280 --> 07:12.080
BSA sniper rifles,
three boxes of hand grenades.

07:12.080 --> 07:13.760
For what purpose?

07:15.440 --> 07:19.640
For eventualities like
the one that is about to occur.

07:19.640 --> 07:22.760
When men come to us
with bad intentions,

07:22.760 --> 07:24.720
the family come together.

07:24.720 --> 07:27.240
Tommy says it's time
you join the family.

07:28.600 --> 07:31.720
But you're not just going to be
a soldier.

07:31.720 --> 07:35.360
You're going to be a general...
some day.

07:41.400 --> 07:43.240
So, I need to ask you
some questions.

07:50.640 --> 07:52.760
What have you ever fired?

07:55.440 --> 07:56.920
Shotgun.

07:59.520 --> 08:00.840
Pistol.

08:00.840 --> 08:02.040
22.

08:03.720 --> 08:06.360
What have you ever killed?

08:06.360 --> 08:08.440
Few rabbits.

08:08.440 --> 08:10.480
Pheasant, partridge. A stag.

08:13.360 --> 08:15.920
Arthur tells me when they were
taking care of some business

08:15.920 --> 08:19.320
at the betting shop,
you ran away.

08:20.360 --> 08:22.440
It was unfair.

08:24.560 --> 08:27.720
Fairness is not
a soldier's concern.

08:27.720 --> 08:29.560
You do what you do.

08:30.720 --> 08:32.680
I already have done.

08:33.880 --> 08:35.560
Fair and square.

08:35.560 --> 08:37.920
I have killed a man.

08:40.000 --> 08:41.960
Tommy's always right.

08:48.520 --> 08:50.880
We were outside
a hospital in Bridgnorth.

08:50.880 --> 08:52.560
In the Black Country.

08:52.560 --> 08:54.600
My mother was dying.

08:54.600 --> 08:58.920
And the orderly
wouldn't give her a bed

08:58.920 --> 09:01.840
cos she was a Gypsy -
she had no insurance.

09:04.160 --> 09:06.200
She never saw the sunrise.

09:08.680 --> 09:11.080
Nor did that man
who denied her.

09:15.240 --> 09:18.240
Just one more thing
we need to know about you.

09:22.080 --> 09:24.360
Can you keep a secret?

09:29.560 --> 09:31.080
I know, brother.

09:41.560 --> 09:43.160
I know.

09:47.120 --> 09:48.880
I know.

09:50.240 --> 09:52.080
I stole your keys.

09:56.240 --> 09:58.080
Tuberculoma.

10:01.800 --> 10:03.720
In your brain.

10:03.720 --> 10:05.400
Yeah.

10:05.400 --> 10:08.080
But I still have time
to do what I need to do.

10:11.280 --> 10:13.480
Fuck you, Tommy.

10:13.480 --> 10:15.680
I don't need anyone to know,
Arthur.

10:17.040 --> 10:18.960
No, you don't, do you?

10:18.960 --> 10:21.040
You don't need anything,
do you?

10:21.040 --> 10:22.480
No, I don't need anything.

10:22.480 --> 10:24.600
I don't need anything.

10:24.600 --> 10:27.240
How long
have we been dead for, eh?

10:27.240 --> 10:29.200
You and me, how long?

10:29.200 --> 10:31.080
At least now
I'll have a certificate.

10:31.080 --> 10:32.560
ARTHUR SCOFFS

10:32.560 --> 10:33.960
Wherever it is,

10:33.960 --> 10:36.520
I'll get the drinks in
and I'll wait for you.

10:39.960 --> 10:42.200
Fuck's sake. Yeah.

10:43.280 --> 10:45.680
All them bullets that missed.

10:45.680 --> 10:48.160
TOMMY CHUCKLES
It's funny, Arthur.

10:48.160 --> 10:50.080
It's funny is what it is.

10:52.160 --> 10:54.400
So don't you fucking weep.

10:56.840 --> 10:58.320
Weep!

10:59.600 --> 11:02.440
When everyone is taken care
of financially,

11:02.440 --> 11:04.960
I will take myself away.
On my own.

11:08.920 --> 11:10.800
I don't want anyone...

11:12.960 --> 11:16.440
..anyone who may or may not
love me...

11:18.080 --> 11:20.560
..to have to see me crawl...

11:21.560 --> 11:23.560
..or grow insane and helpless.

11:23.560 --> 11:28.040
It would be a cruelty to me
and to them.

11:28.040 --> 11:33.720
By the time people know
the truth, I will be gone.

11:35.760 --> 11:37.920
What about Lizzie?

11:37.920 --> 11:40.200
I have some papers
I need you to sign

11:40.200 --> 11:42.080
on behalf of the company.

11:42.080 --> 11:43.960
Told Lizzie?

11:43.960 --> 11:46.920
I'm working
with the housing minister.

11:46.920 --> 11:48.920
I will be allocating contracts,

11:48.920 --> 11:51.400
construction contracts,
worth Â£10 million.

11:51.400 --> 11:53.240
You haven't told Lizzie?

11:53.240 --> 11:55.080
Some of the contracts
I will be allocating

11:55.080 --> 11:57.080
are with companies
in which we have an interest.

11:57.080 --> 11:59.600
Fuck you and your contracts!

11:59.600 --> 12:03.120
So the Shelby Company Limited
will continue to earn money.

12:04.200 --> 12:07.920
But mostly, Arthur, I'm doing it
because it's a good thing.

12:07.920 --> 12:10.200
Building houses. Oh...

12:10.200 --> 12:13.680
Yeah, for ordinary working people...
Oh, yeah, good for you. Fuckin'...

12:13.680 --> 12:16.560
..in the interests
of a fairer future.

12:16.560 --> 12:21.000
And before that,
I will be going to Canada

12:21.000 --> 12:23.800
to collect payment
for the shipment - Â£5 million!

12:23.800 --> 12:25.600
Oh, five fucking million?

12:25.600 --> 12:29.000
Which I will share
among the Shelby family.

12:31.120 --> 12:32.800
And that will be my legacy.

12:32.800 --> 12:35.520
Instead of me,
there will be money.

12:35.520 --> 12:37.360
Because for most
of the people

12:37.360 --> 12:39.600
who are close to me,
that is what I am!

12:39.600 --> 12:42.320
Fucking money.
That is my agency.

12:42.320 --> 12:45.640
Is that all you think you are,
eh? Hmm?

12:47.360 --> 12:49.120
Stand up.

12:52.320 --> 12:54.600
You heard me.

12:54.600 --> 12:55.680
Stand up.

12:56.680 --> 12:58.440
On your feet.

12:58.440 --> 13:00.720
On your fucking feet. Arthur...

13:00.720 --> 13:03.120
On your feet, Soldier.
On your feet.

13:03.120 --> 13:04.920
Stand the fuck up! Come here.

13:08.240 --> 13:10.240
No!

13:10.240 --> 13:11.520
No.

13:12.560 --> 13:14.040
You hear me?

13:14.040 --> 13:15.440
Enough.

13:17.280 --> 13:18.680
Enough!

13:26.120 --> 13:27.800
Now you know.

13:29.680 --> 13:31.240
You tell no-one else...

13:32.720 --> 13:34.120
..until I am gone.

13:34.120 --> 13:35.720
Until you're gone, yeah?

13:39.120 --> 13:42.040
When the time comes,
I'll call you.

13:45.280 --> 13:48.120
I'll tell you where.
It'll be a wagon.

13:48.120 --> 13:50.720
Fuck your wagon!

13:50.720 --> 13:52.560
You light the flame.

13:52.560 --> 13:55.760
You bring Charlie and Curly
and no-one else.

13:57.000 --> 13:58.720
Get drunk.

13:58.720 --> 14:00.680
Rake the ashes
for silver and gold.

14:00.680 --> 14:02.360
Fuck you!

14:03.560 --> 14:05.760
And your fucking plans!

14:20.360 --> 14:23.600
That time,
I did let you fucking win.

14:30.760 --> 14:31.800
John...

14:35.280 --> 14:37.280
Fuckin' you, John.

14:40.880 --> 14:43.040
Fuckin' both of you.

14:44.440 --> 14:45.840
Arthur...

14:47.200 --> 14:49.160
Arthur.

14:49.160 --> 14:51.520
Come here. Come here.
Come here. Come here.

14:51.520 --> 14:53.800
ARTHUR SOBS
Come here.

14:53.800 --> 14:55.280
Come here.

14:56.560 --> 14:58.320
Come here.

14:58.320 --> 14:59.760
Let me see your eyes.

14:59.760 --> 15:02.520
I'm clean, man.

15:02.520 --> 15:05.200
The dragon's fucking gone.

15:05.200 --> 15:09.040
Thanks to you. Fucking...
Fucking thanks to you.

15:35.720 --> 15:37.640
You all right?

15:37.640 --> 15:38.960
Come on.

15:40.040 --> 15:43.280
Fucking...
Hey, I'm still fucking here.

15:43.280 --> 15:46.080
Pull yourself together,
come on. We have work to do.

15:47.800 --> 15:49.200
Come on!

16:03.480 --> 16:05.640
DOOR OPENS

16:12.360 --> 16:15.960
You're sure you want Billy?
I had to shut up the shop.

16:15.960 --> 16:18.640
Yes. We want Billy.

16:18.640 --> 16:20.400
Sit down, Billy.

16:25.320 --> 16:27.840
Thank you for inviting me,
Mr Shelby.

16:29.880 --> 16:32.160
Good to see you again, Billy.

16:38.400 --> 16:42.440
No. Mary says
not until after six o'clock.

16:47.920 --> 16:51.120
He said to tell his father
he feels OK about it.

16:51.120 --> 16:53.920
Good. Shut the door, Duke.

17:03.560 --> 17:05.560
Now, we are all gathered...

17:07.040 --> 17:08.080
...and those...

17:13.520 --> 17:17.880
Apologies, Mr Shelby,
I still don't speak the lingo.

17:17.880 --> 17:21.000
Well, Finn here never even
bothered to learn it.

17:21.000 --> 17:22.680
I heard "tachipen".

17:22.680 --> 17:26.000
Truth. You said something
about the truth.

17:26.000 --> 17:29.000
Truth. The truth is...

17:29.000 --> 17:31.440
..I called men here
that I could trust...

17:31.440 --> 17:33.560
..because I will be going away.

17:35.680 --> 17:38.240
I have to collect payment
for a shipment of goods

17:38.240 --> 17:42.120
which left Liverpool
ten days ago. Payment from who?

17:42.120 --> 17:44.600
South Boston Irish, Finn.

17:45.760 --> 17:47.400
Bootleggers.

17:49.520 --> 17:51.640
Are you going alone?

17:51.640 --> 17:54.520
Johnny Dogs has already sailed
for Canada.

17:54.520 --> 17:56.640
Michael will be there.

17:56.640 --> 17:58.280
Michael is family.

17:59.280 --> 18:01.960
Michael will be my guarantee
of safety.

18:01.960 --> 18:05.320
But while I'm away,
I have a job for you all.

18:05.320 --> 18:07.840
I need you to go
to Arrow House.

18:07.840 --> 18:09.960
I will be leaving Arrow House
for good,

18:09.960 --> 18:12.600
and there are things
that need removing.

18:12.600 --> 18:14.720
I need men that I can trust.

18:14.720 --> 18:17.200
There is cash,
there is valuables.

18:17.200 --> 18:19.600
There is information
about important people

18:19.600 --> 18:21.480
that has more value than gold.

18:23.000 --> 18:26.160
There are also bodies buried
in the grounds

18:26.160 --> 18:27.640
which need digging up

18:27.640 --> 18:29.880
before the contractors
start moving earth.

18:29.880 --> 18:31.880
Isiah, you will be in charge.

18:33.280 --> 18:35.400
In Arrow House,
there is a wine cellar.

18:35.400 --> 18:38.000
In that wine cellar,
there are fine French wines

18:38.000 --> 18:40.200
that are worth more
than a man's life.

18:40.200 --> 18:43.320
You are welcome to them, boys,
it'll be like a...

18:43.320 --> 18:45.320
..be like a farewell party.

18:46.520 --> 18:48.960
Are you ready for the party,
son?

18:53.120 --> 18:56.680
Tachipen.
The fucking truth again.

18:58.120 --> 19:01.160
What truth? You'll need shovels,
you'll need boxes,

19:01.160 --> 19:03.440
and you'll take the bones
to Mr Patches

19:03.440 --> 19:06.080
to put in the furnace
at Greenham's.

19:06.080 --> 19:08.120
Got it?

19:08.120 --> 19:09.960
Right. Any questions?

19:09.960 --> 19:12.520
Yeah. If it's a party,
can we bring girls?

19:12.520 --> 19:13.760
BILLY CHUCKLES

19:13.760 --> 19:16.800
No, Billy. All the fun will be
laid on for you.

19:19.040 --> 19:21.440
So, when is the party, Tom?

19:26.320 --> 19:28.000
Mr Shelby.

19:29.080 --> 19:30.920
Party's next Sunday, Billy.

19:32.240 --> 19:34.600
You mean this Sunday?

19:34.600 --> 19:36.440
Yeah.

19:36.440 --> 19:39.560
And while you're
digging fucking holes,

19:39.560 --> 19:42.520
I'll be here drinking
champagne with my wife.

19:42.520 --> 19:44.680
It's our wedding anniversary.

19:44.680 --> 19:45.920
Right.

19:45.920 --> 19:48.920
Oh, and, Finn, by the way,

19:48.920 --> 19:52.560
please explain to, erm,
what's her name?

19:52.560 --> 19:55.440
Mary. Mary? Yes. Is it Mary?

19:55.440 --> 19:59.120
Please explain to Mary
that you are a Shelby.

19:59.120 --> 20:01.360
It says it here
on the back of your watch.

20:01.360 --> 20:04.040
Have a look - Shelby. Look.

20:04.040 --> 20:07.240
This means you own the watch,

20:07.240 --> 20:09.080
the watch doesn't own you.

20:09.080 --> 20:12.160
The clock strikes six
when you fucking tell it to.

20:12.160 --> 20:13.760
Have a whiskey.

20:15.400 --> 20:17.200
Enjoy the party, boys.

20:20.680 --> 20:22.720
JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS

20:32.000 --> 20:34.880
SHE SIGHS
Want a drink, baby?

20:34.880 --> 20:36.240
No.

20:36.240 --> 20:38.480
Drinking water like Tommy, huh?

20:40.960 --> 20:44.080
Until this thing is done,
I need a clear head.

20:49.240 --> 20:51.920
PHONE RINGS

20:51.920 --> 20:53.320
Leave it.

21:08.280 --> 21:10.840
Yeah?

21:10.840 --> 21:12.040
Good.

21:13.080 --> 21:14.560
That's good.

21:16.000 --> 21:18.080
Look, I've got to go.

21:19.800 --> 21:22.480
Good news, Michael. Listen.

21:23.960 --> 21:27.720
That was our informant
in Birmingham.

21:27.720 --> 21:31.640
The Shelby men will all be together
on Sunday.

21:31.640 --> 21:33.960
But Arthur will be having
dinner with his wife

21:33.960 --> 21:35.880
at the bar
at the Garrison Tavern.

21:42.240 --> 21:45.840
As I recall, the Shelby table is
right next to the windows, correct?

21:45.840 --> 21:48.640
Every table's a Shelby table.
Yes, but...

21:49.880 --> 21:53.280
...maybe our people
could just drive by and...

21:53.280 --> 21:56.800
..shoot Arthur through the glass
without even getting out of the car.

21:58.720 --> 22:00.480
Michael...

22:01.520 --> 22:04.080
..we've talked about this -
there's no other choice.

22:04.080 --> 22:06.720
This business is between me
and Tommy.

22:06.720 --> 22:10.280
Yes, and when you kill Tommy,

22:10.280 --> 22:12.120
Arthur will come after you.

22:13.400 --> 22:14.880
He has to die too.

22:17.760 --> 22:20.400
If Arthur's in a bar,
he'll be drunk.

22:21.520 --> 22:23.280
Or worse.

22:23.280 --> 22:25.600
At least he'll die without pain.

22:32.600 --> 22:34.160
Who'll do the killing?

22:36.360 --> 22:39.040
Tommy's working
with a faction of the IRA.

22:39.040 --> 22:41.240
Connor has connections.

22:41.240 --> 22:42.600
They made a deal.

22:44.080 --> 22:47.280
A favour in return for guns.

22:48.840 --> 22:50.280
But, Michael...

22:52.160 --> 22:54.120
..whilst the assassin's
in this city...

22:55.640 --> 22:57.680
..Tommy has a son.

22:57.680 --> 22:59.240
He's a kid.

22:59.240 --> 23:00.640
Kids grow up.

