just going to die in your bed?

1:00:37.360 --> 1:00:40.280
I'm not going to die in bed, Alfie.
Who fucking dies in bed?

1:00:40.280 --> 1:00:43.080
Good people die in their bed,
Tommy. Good people.

1:00:43.080 --> 1:00:44.560
Good people, eh? Hmm.

1:00:45.920 --> 1:00:47.640
Good people.

1:00:47.640 --> 1:00:49.520
And yet here we are, Alfie,

1:00:49.520 --> 1:00:52.800
after all this time,
just you and me.

1:00:55.720 --> 1:00:57.760
And I crossed the line.

1:01:00.840 --> 1:01:02.320
Michael.

1:01:04.040 --> 1:01:05.520
Polly.

1:01:07.720 --> 1:01:09.520
Ruby.

1:01:11.600 --> 1:01:17.360
Tommy, if you are about
to express profound emotion,

1:01:17.360 --> 1:01:20.160
you might be better served
expressing it

1:01:20.160 --> 1:01:22.800
to someone
who gives a fuck,

1:01:22.800 --> 1:01:26.040
or perhaps to somebody
who is being paid

1:01:26.040 --> 1:01:28.000
to pretend to have to.

1:01:28.000 --> 1:01:32.200
Like a fucking nurse.
Or a priest! Someone.

1:01:34.480 --> 1:01:36.760
And as for death,

1:01:36.760 --> 1:01:39.200
speaking as someone
who has been dead

1:01:39.200 --> 1:01:41.440
for a number of years,

1:01:41.440 --> 1:01:44.880
I can only
heartily recommend it.

1:01:44.880 --> 1:01:49.280
Well, Alfie,
your opera is complete.

1:01:55.960 --> 1:01:59.280
Shall we go
and witness the final act?

1:02:45.040 --> 1:02:47.400
Whenever you're ready, boys.

1:03:29.720 --> 1:03:31.120
That's enough.

1:03:31.120 --> 1:03:32.960
HE CLEARS HIS THROAT

1:03:32.960 --> 1:03:34.680
Thank you all for coming.

1:03:36.360 --> 1:03:38.120
Well, at least
I can say that, er...

1:03:39.680 --> 1:03:41.880
..I am one of those rare politicians

1:03:41.880 --> 1:03:43.880
who actually makes good
on his promises.

1:03:45.600 --> 1:03:47.480
Country estate -

1:03:47.480 --> 1:03:51.800
requisitioned to make way
for houses for working people.

1:03:51.800 --> 1:03:54.960
I improved my own home
with good intentions

1:03:54.960 --> 1:03:57.560
and 1,500lb of dynamite.

1:04:02.520 --> 1:04:04.040
Now I'm back where we began...

1:04:05.720 --> 1:04:07.400
..with horses and caravans...

1:04:09.120 --> 1:04:11.800
..vagabonds and thieves.

1:04:15.280 --> 1:04:17.400
Frances, sit down, please.

1:04:26.800 --> 1:04:29.920
I'd like to raise a toast.

1:04:29.920 --> 1:04:31.200
A simple toast.

1:04:34.560 --> 1:04:36.000
To family.

1:04:36.000 --> 1:04:37.720
To family. To family.

1:04:37.720 --> 1:04:41.960
Sometimes it is shelter
from the storm.

1:04:43.680 --> 1:04:46.280
Sometimes it is
the storm itself.

1:04:56.920 --> 1:04:59.320
I'm planning on going away
for a bit.

1:05:00.360 --> 1:05:02.080
After I'm gone...

1:05:05.440 --> 1:05:07.800
Ada...

1:05:07.800 --> 1:05:09.160
..in this family...

1:05:10.480 --> 1:05:12.880
..it was you who was born
to be a politician, not me.

1:05:14.480 --> 1:05:15.960
Remember that.

1:05:17.400 --> 1:05:19.960
And if ever a seat
is to become available

1:05:19.960 --> 1:05:22.400
in this ugly old city,
you should run.

1:05:22.400 --> 1:05:23.920
SHE LAUGHS

1:05:23.920 --> 1:05:25.000
Where's Arthur?

1:05:25.000 --> 1:05:28.320
He went for a walk
down the river.

1:05:28.320 --> 1:05:30.600
He said he's not good
at farewells

1:05:30.600 --> 1:05:33.120
so he's decided to
go catch a trout instead.

1:05:36.560 --> 1:05:38.680
He told me to tell you that...

1:05:40.520 --> 1:05:43.560
"Where you're going, Tommy,
there will I be...

1:05:44.720 --> 1:05:47.360
"..very soon. Love, Arthur."

1:05:54.480 --> 1:05:57.520
How does Arthur know
where you're going, Tommy?

1:05:59.000 --> 1:06:01.760
You watch him, Linda.

1:06:01.760 --> 1:06:03.680
You love him.

1:06:07.680 --> 1:06:11.840
Charles, I want you
to look after your mum.

1:06:11.840 --> 1:06:15.040
You tell her I'm sorry,
you hear me?

1:06:20.880 --> 1:06:22.960
I want you to be the bes...

1:06:27.360 --> 1:06:30.760
Exactly how long
are you going away for, Tommy?

1:06:41.240 --> 1:06:42.840
Thanks, Curly.

1:06:47.960 --> 1:06:50.040
HE WHISPERS

1:07:00.160 --> 1:07:01.880
Tom, the horse.

1:07:01.880 --> 1:07:03.520
Shut up, Curly.

1:07:10.600 --> 1:07:13.200
Is she hitched, Johnny?

1:07:13.200 --> 1:07:17.320
Tommy, you tell me right now,
where are you going?

1:07:17.320 --> 1:07:20.240
You have to carry the bucket
on your own this time, Ada.

1:07:20.240 --> 1:07:22.120
Tommy, you come to me
with everything.

1:07:22.120 --> 1:07:25.520
You always come to me. Not this
time. Not this one, sister.

1:07:25.520 --> 1:07:28.640
What the fuck does that mean?
Where are you going?

1:07:30.320 --> 1:07:32.320
Tommy!

